{"key":"processedPost-6733780","value":{"id":6733780,"first":6733366,"last":6737723,"when":1175412527,"utime":"04/01/07 10:28 AM","content":"It's been done many times.  The plants don't do well in the high humidity, usually getting powdery mildew on the leaves, and they also generally bring bugs you don't want, which then munch on your fungi.<br />As for helping with the CO2/O2, forget it.  The mycelium produces way more CO2 than plants can metabolize, and the amount of plants that would fit in a mini-greenhouse won't do squat as far as helping with O2 for the mushrooms.<br />They look cool in a terrarium though.<br />RR<br /><a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/05-15/339830342-mex_0005a.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/05-15/339830342-thumb_mex_0005a.jpg\"></a>","title":"Re: anybody ever put plants in the fruiting chamber?"}}